Pin nvidia-cutlass-dsl (+ its two libs wheels) to an exact, known-good version.

Root cause (2026-07-09): NVIDIA has shipped different wheel CONTENT under the
SAME version number. Two builds of the 0.5.14-sm121 image six days apart
(2026-06-29 vs 2026-07-06) both resolved nvidia-cutlass-dsl==4.5.2 yet ended up
with different cutlass/_mlir generated binding files (_llvm_ops_gen.py sha
mismatch). The newer variant is internally inconsistent: its own
cutlass_dsl/tvm_ffi_provider.py passes data=[] to llvm.mlir_global_dtors(),
whose ODS-generated binding in that same wheel lacks the parameter. Every FRESH
CuTe-DSL JIT compile then dies with

    DSLRuntimeError: ICE ... mlir_global_dtors() got an unexpected keyword
    argument 'data'

first hit in practice: flashinfer's rmsnorm_cute during SGLang CUDA-graph
warmup -> scheduler crash-loop on ANY model (verified on both the Nemotron head
and the Qwen3-VL vision instance). flashinfer only requires
nvidia-cutlass-dsl>=4.5.0 (open-ended), so every rebuild re-resolves this
transitively. 4.5.3 (released 2026-07-08) restores consistency — verified by
in-pod install on the broken image (compile OK).

Mirrors the dockerfile-kernels-pin.patch mechanism: ARG + gated force-reinstall
RUN in the builder stage (BEFORE directory_split2.sh so the pinned files are
carried into the runtime stage). --no-deps + all three wheels pinned explicitly
(meta + libs-base + libs-cu13 share one version) so nothing else is touched;
--force-reinstall so the pin wins even over a same-version-different-bytes
install. Empty CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION = no-op.

Applied AFTER dockerfile-kernels-pin.patch and dockerfile-audio-deps.patch (it
anchors on the audio-deps block). The recipe drives it via the
CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION variable (see sglang-0.5.14-sm121.recipe delta note 7).

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly in the local clone of
scitrera/cuda-containers.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -269,6 +269,26 @@
         uv pip install ${AUDIO_DEPS}; \
     fi

+# dgxarley: pin nvidia-cutlass-dsl to an exact, known-good version. NVIDIA has
+# shipped different wheel content under the SAME version number (two builds
+# both resolving ==4.5.2 got different cutlass/_mlir bindings; the later one
+# passes data=[] to an llvm.mlir_global_dtors() binding without that param ->
+# "ICE ... unexpected keyword argument 'data'" on every fresh CuTe-DSL JIT
+# compile, first hit flashinfer rmsnorm_cute in CUDA-graph warmup; fixed
+# upstream in 4.5.3, 2026-07-08). Force-reinstall of the meta package + BOTH
+# libs wheels (--no-deps, exact ==) so the pin wins even over a
+# same-version-different-bytes install. Empty = no-op.
+# See patches/dockerfile-cutlass-dsl-pin.patch.
+ARG CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION=""
+RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
+    if [ -n "$CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION" ]; then \
+        echo "=== Pinning nvidia-cutlass-dsl==${CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION} ==="; \
+        uv pip install --force-reinstall --no-deps \
+            "nvidia-cutlass-dsl==${CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION}" \
+            "nvidia-cutlass-dsl-libs-base==${CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION}" \
+            "nvidia-cutlass-dsl-libs-cu13==${CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION}"; \
+    fi
+
 # SM121 (DGX Spark GB10) shared memory fix for cutlass_moe_fp4.
 # Patches run_fp4_blockwise_scaled_group_mm_sm120() in the JIT-compiled
 # nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh to use KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedCooperative
